Mortal Engines is the first of four novels in Philip Reeve's quartet of the same name, The book focuses on a futuristic, steampunk version of a London, now a giant machine striving to survive on a world running out of resources. The book has won a Nestl√© Smarties Book Prize and was shortlisted for the 2002 Whitbread Award. Recommended for those seeking to venture into the steampunk genre for the first time. Called a classic by those who've read it, " Where Charles Dickens, meets Star Wars..." Booklist. " The setting a modern H.G. Wells or Jules Vern novel... Reminiscent of the Time Machine, Twenty Thousand Leagues Under the Sea and From the Earth to the Moon." Publisher's Weekly.